description: Manage inbound endpoint with dns resolver.

commands.name: az dns-resolver inbound-endpoint create
commands.summary: Create an inbound endpoint for a DNS resolver.
commands.syntax:
az dns-resolver inbound-endpoint create --dns-resolver-name
                                        --inbound-endpoint-name
                                        --ip-configurations
                                        --resource-group
                                        [--if-match]
                                        [--if-none-match]
                                        [--location]
                                        [--no-wait {0, 1, f, false, n, no, t, true, y, yes}]
                                        [--tags]

commands.name: az dns-resolver inbound-endpoint delete
commands.summary: Deletes an inbound endpoint for a DNS resolver. WARNING: This operation cannot be undone.
commands.syntax:
az dns-resolver inbound-endpoint delete [--dns-resolver-name]
                                        [--ids]
                                        [--if-match]
                                        [--inbound-endpoint-name]
                                        [--no-wait {0, 1, f, false, n, no, t, true, y, yes}]
                                        [--resource-group]
                                        [--subscription]
                                        [--yes]

commands.name: az dns-resolver inbound-endpoint list
commands.summary: Lists inbound endpoints for a DNS resolver.

commands.name: az dns-resolver inbound-endpoint show
commands.summary: Gets properties of an inbound endpoint for a DNS resolver.

commands.name: az dns-resolver inbound-endpoint update
commands.summary: Updates an inbound endpoint for a DNS resolver.
commands.syntax:
az dns-resolver inbound-endpoint update [--add]
                                        [--dns-resolver-name]
                                        [--force-string {0, 1, f, false, n, no, t, true, y, yes}]
                                        [--ids]
                                        [--if-match]
                                        [--inbound-endpoint-name]
                                        [--no-wait {0, 1, f, false, n, no, t, true, y, yes}]
                                        [--remove]
                                        [--resource-group]
                                        [--set]
                                        [--subscription]
                                        [--tags]

commands.name: az dns-resolver inbound-endpoint wait
commands.summary: Place the CLI in a waiting state until a condition is met.
